node.text:
Prepare yourselves... @whatsthomaseating and I challenged each other to a blind taste test of the new @edys @dreyers Rocky Road Collection and honestly, I've never loved my job more!! Take a wild guess who has the better palate.... #ad

If you're down to get crazy and try all the insanely delish flavors, THIS IS YOUR MOMENT. Now through Wednesday, June 9, buy just one full-size flavor from the EDY'S or Dreyer’s recently launched and get the rest of the collection for free when you share a photo of your ice cream on Instagram. Details on how to enter are below! Which flavor would you try first?

🍦 Purchase one of the six Rocky Road Collection flavors at a national grocery retailer near you. Mocha Almond Avenue, Brownie Brick Road, Cookie Cobblestone, Chocolate Peanut Butter Park, Salted Caramel Pretzel Path and/or The Original Rocky Road
🍦 Share a photo of your purchase on Instagram via an in-feed post or Instagram story using the #NationalRockyRoadDay. Can’t make it to the store? No problem! Just comment on @edys or @dreyers promotion post using #NationalRockyRoadDay with one sentence about which flavor of the Rocky Road Collection you’re most excited to try and why.
🍦 Make sure you’re following @edys and @dreyers and tag the handles in your post. Don’t forget to set your profile to Public so they can see your entry!
🍦 EDY'S (Dreyer's) will direct message eligible entrants while supplies last with next steps on how to claim their free ice cream!
NO PURCHASE NECESSARY. Limit to one entry per person. Open to legal residents of the 50 United States (D.C), 13 and older. Entries must be received by 11:59pm PDT on 6/9/21. For Official Rules, go to the link in the @edys @dreyers bio.

node.text:
Guess what - the construction is done!! We might not have furniture but who cares!! Enjoy part 5 of our home reno and stay tuned because you'll see what's happening next towards the end!!
Resources for everything we discussed:
Contractor: @lyonsdevelopment
Designers: @thea_home
Appliances: @subzeroandwolf
Kitchen + Bathroom Fixtures: @rejuvenation
Custom Bar: @ericervinwoodwork
Custom art: @fiftyoneandahalf 
Backsplash Tile: @fireclaytile
Main Bathroom Paint: @portolapaints Lime Wash
Fancy Schmancy Toilet: @kohler 
Window Treatments: @theshadestore 
Cabinet Maker: @donscabinets
Painting: @tpg_inc
Nursery: @crateandkids
Windows and Doors: @pellawindows 
Floors: unsure of brand but they are a light oak

node.text: Currently obsessing over this watermelon peach salad with feta and mint!! It’s bright and flavorful and requires zero actual cooking which is key, bc it’s HOT AF here in LA! Get this and a slew of my other fav no-cook meals over on WGC https://whatsgabycooking.com/19-no-cook-summer-meals/

node.text:
Chicken Parm Pasta on deck for dinner this week - one of my all time favorite recipes!! Stepping it up a few notches tonight with the new Artisan Ingredients pasta sauce from @mezzetta!! Here's the deal - if you're craving a trip to Italy but it's not in the cards for you at the moment, you're going to want to make this immediately! This Mezzetta sauce is amping up the flavor with authentic Parmigiano Reggiano cheese from the Emilia-Romagna region of Italy that’s aged for 12 months and I don't know anyone who's gonna be mad at that! Recipe is below! xx 

1 tbsp olive oil
1 onion, diced 
3 to 4 cloves garlic, finely chopped 
1/2 teaspoon red pepper flakes
1 1/4 pounds ground chicken
2 tsp Italian seasoning 
Kosher salt and freshly cracked black pepper
1 (26-ounce) jar Mezzetta Parmigiano Reggiano marinara sauce
1 cup shredded Parmesan cheese, plus more to garnish
1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese
12 ounces pappardelle pasta 
fresh basil leaves

Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onion, garlic and red pepper flakes and cook for 2 to 3 minutes, until the garlic is fragrant. Add the ground chicken and Italian seasoning and season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up the chicken with the back of a wooden spoon, until it is in small pieces. Continue to cook until the chicken is cooked through, about 10 more minutes.
Add the Mezzetta sauce, bring to a simmer, then reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer for 20 minutes. Reduce the heat to low, add the Parmesan and mozzarella cheeses, and stir to combine. Taste and adjust the salt and pepper as needed. While the sauce is simmering, cook the pasta according to the package directions for al dente. Drain the pasta and transfer to the skillet with the meat sauce. Stir to coat the pasta in the sauce and serve garnished with basil leaves and additional Parmesan
